    a: "On most mid-tier double ovens past year 8, yes. Lower fails first by 3 to 4 years; the upper is 60 to 80% along the same wear curve when the lower goes. Adding the upper element costs $80 to $160 in parts, no extra labor (we're already inside the unit), and saves a full second service call within 12 to 24 months. We always offer it as an option; never push it.",
  },
  {
    q: "What's the price difference for double-oven repairs vs single?",
    a: "Diagnostic stays $89. Repair labor on doubles runs $400 to $600 access labor uplift (vs $200 to $300 single) because pulling a 30-inch double weighs 220 to 320 lbs and requires two techs. Parts for paired-replacement strategies (both elements, both hinge sets) double the parts line but no extra labor. We quote it explicitly before any work starts.",
