        <tr><td>Lower bake element (mid-tier)</td><td>$180 to $340</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Lower bake element (pro-tier)</td><td>$440 to $780</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Paired bake element replacement (both cavities, mid-tier)</td><td>$280 to $480</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Paired bake element replacement (both cavities, pro-tier)</td><td>$720 to $1,200</td></tr>
        <tr><td>RTD temperature sensor (per cavity)</td><td>$120 to $260</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Bake relay / lower-circuit control board (mid-tier full board)</td><td>$440 to $720</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Bake relay / lower-circuit control board (pro-tier full board)</td><td>$1,200 to $2,400</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Hinge paired replacement (both pairs, mid-tier)</td><td>$340 to $580</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Hinge paired replacement (both pairs, pro-tier)</td><td>$1,000 to $1,400</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Built-in access labor uplift (double, two-tech)</td><td>$400 to $600</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Multi-component repair</td><td>$780 to $2,400</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Warranty</td><td>90 days parts plus labor</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>If your unit is still in manufacturer warranty (Wolf 2-year, Miele/BSH/GE/KitchenAid 1-year-plus-extended), the $89 diagnostic plus written report is often all you pay; the manufacturer's authorized service handles the actual repair under warranty.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 06 WHY US -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">06 · Why homeowners call us</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Seven reasons.</h2>

    <ul class="why-list">
      <li><strong>Manufacturer warranty submission help.</strong> Wolf 2-year, Miele extended, BSH, GE, KitchenAid. We do the diagnostic and report; you save the repair charge.</li>
      <li><strong>Lower-fails-first diagnostic specialty.</strong> Most common double-oven call; we know the configuration cold.</li>
      <li><strong>Paired replacement strategy when warranted.</strong> Lower plus proactive upper saves a second service call past year 8.</li>
      <li><strong>Two-tech access on 220 to 320 lb units.</strong> Doubles need two people. Quoted in writing before work starts.</li>
      <li><strong>Brand-specific F-code knowledge.</strong> Wolf, Miele, Thermador, GE Profile/Monogram, KitchenAid, Whirlpool all have different F-code dictionaries; we cross-reference.</li>
      <li><strong>BHGS Licensed #A49573 and EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410).</strong> See our <a href="/credentials/licensed/">licensing page</a>. Our license number gives manufacturer claims desks credibility for diagnostic reports.</li>
      <li><strong>$89 residential diagnostic, no after-hours surcharge.</strong> Same-day across LA, OC, Ventura.</li>
    </ul>
